------------------------------------------------------------------------
Material Symbols / Material Icons
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Flare's built-in SVG icon set (Flare.Components: FlareIcons) contains icon
artwork derived from Google's Material Symbols / Material Icons.

  Source:  https://github.com/google/material-design-icons
  License: Apache License, Version 2.0
           https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

The bundled paths are shipped as inline SVG so Flare's default component
chrome renders without an external icon font. Optional Material Symbols
font usage (FlareMaterialIcon) additionally relies on the Material Symbols
font, loaded by the host application.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Font Awesome (optional package Flare.Icons.FontAwesome)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
FlareFontAwesomeIcon emits Font Awesome CSS classes; it bundles no Font
Awesome artwork or fonts. The host application supplies a Font Awesome
stylesheet (Free or Pro), subject to Font Awesome's own license.

  https://fontawesome.com/license

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fluent UI System Icons (optional package Flare.Icons.Fluent)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Flare.Icons.Fluent bundles a curated set of Fluent UI System Icons SVG
artwork (the FluentIcons catalog), generated by tools/FluentIconGen from
Microsoft's icon package. FlareFluentIcon also renders any Fluent SVG the
consumer supplies via its Data property.

  Source:  https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui-system-icons
  License: MIT License
